<emphasis id="77E4EA9A2B654909FF0B64C75221FAFD" bold="true" box="[199,353,1256,1282]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Distribution.</emphasis>
This is the first record for 
<collectingCountry id="3D8776182B654909FD4B64C7505BFAFD" box="[647,795,1256,1282]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry id="3D8776182B654909FBD764C757D3FAFD" box="[1051,1171,1256,1282]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(as “ 
<collectingCountry id="3D8776182B654909FB0564C75678FAFC" box="[1225,1336,1256,1283]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Rhodesia</collectingCountry>
”) (
<bibRefCitation id="21014B792B654909FA9464C75228FAD8" author="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="488 - 510" refId="ref40306" refString="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1980) 38. Family Syrphidae. In: Crosskey R. W. (Ed.), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afro- tropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 488 - 510." type="book chapter" year="1980">Smith &amp; Vockeroth 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="21014B792B654909FEBF6523517FFAD8" author="Whittington, A. E." box="[371,575,1292,1319]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="579 - 607" refId="ref41868" refString="Whittington, A. E. (2003) The Afrotropical Syrphidae fauna: an assessment. Studia dipterologica, 10 (2), 579 - 607." type="journal article" year="2003">Whittington 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="452F36882B654909FF5B655752B6FA6D" blockId="14.[151,502,1400,1427]" box="[151,502,1400,1427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="77E4EA9A2B654909FF5B655752B6FA6D" bold="true" box="[151,502,1400,1427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
